  "texts": [
    "The execution time of the DT is lower, with the BRCG explainer being even intractable for 10,000 features.",
    "Anchors also exhibit short execution times, typically 1 to 5 s, even when dealing with 10,000 features.",
    "Being a cohort explainer, we measure the average rule coverage of a sample of 50 instances instead of the coverage on the whole dataset.",
    "Increasing the number of features, the coverage decreases while the average rule correctness on 50 rules increases.",
    "A potential interpretation of this could be that, by using more features, Anchors generate more precise rules with less common words, which consequently have lower coverage over the data.In Table 4 we can observe the results for feature-based explainers."
